
STM NUCLEO-G071RB  Board  with STM32G071RB

	- 128 KB Flash
	- 36 KB RAM
	- Embedded ST-LINK
	- Virtual COM port interface on USB 
	
	
;------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hardware and configuration for STM32G071RB:
;------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Connect to onboard USB Micro-B connector to power up and flash the chip.
  Virtual COM port is connected to PA2 (TX) and PA3 (RX).

  Use a ST-LINK Utility such as:
	- STM32 CubeProgrammer
	- Load the mecrisp-stellaris-stm32g071rb.bin
	- Start programming

  On startup, this runs with internal 16 MHz HSI clock.

